# Line-ending policy for cross-platform reproducibility
# (integration-hardening onboarding pre-mortem, A6).
#
# Text is normalized to LF in the repository. Byte-exact fixtures are pinned so
# no core.autocrlf variant (true on Windows, input on Linux) can alter them at
# checkout — the byte-equality gates must round-trip unchanged. The live probe
# seed files are written at runtime with explicit LF bytes (write_bytes), so
# they never pass through git checkout and need no attribute here.

* text=auto

# Byte-exact fixtures — recorded JSONL the tests read and round-trip.
tests/observe/fixtures/** -text

# Formats where LF is load-bearing regardless of platform.
*.sh   text eol=lf
*.txt  text eol=lf
*.yaml text eol=lf
*.yml  text eol=lf

# Binaries — never apply eol or diff conversion.
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.gif binary
*.ico binary
